        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 2:43PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Hendersonville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chimney Rock State Park, Dana, Lake Adger, Edneyville, and Mill
Spring.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
